                    <span>My position was, I had done some C++ for a few weeks, and wanted to move onto bigger things.<P>Windows programs, networking, multiplayer games all interested me. This book helped me understand all the above.<P>I like the amusing comments, cartoons and the way the book is styled. It keeps me interested and never bores me.<P>Overall a fantastic read and I personally, learned a lot without the pain, maybe not for the super-advanced programmer, but great if you havn't been doing C++ for 20 years.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A great book for beginners and intermediate programmers</div>
